mfortability while dining the table should not be too high.";i:15;s:103:"As a result most dining tables are between 28 and 30 inches from the floor to the surface of the table.";i:16;s:104:"While there are other heights available youll find the widest selection of styles finishes and sizes of.";i:17;s:68:"A typical kitchen table is between 28 and 30 inches 711 762 cm tall.";i:18;s:104:"The exact height of a table typically depends on its style function and type of chair that goes with it.";i:19;s:121:"Bar style tables are generally either 36 inches 914 cm tall or the full bar height of 42 inches 1066 cm above the ground.";i:20;s:29:"BSEN1729 Parts 1 2 Explained.";i:21;s:96:"Do you need help deciding on the height of table you require and the corresponding chair height.";i:22;s:145:"This simple to use height guide illustrates the recommended heights for both tabling and seating in accordance with the European standard EN1729.";i:23;s:23:"Chair and table height.";i:24;s:65:"Chair seat height is the most important calculation you can make.";i:25;s:139:"If a childs feet are flat on the floor and her knees are bent at a 90º angle you have the correct chair for ergonomic comfortable seating.";i:26;s:70:"The chart on the right gives you chair height recom-mendations by age.";i:27;s:27:"Then pick a table to match.";i:28;s:37:"In most cases table tops should be 8.";i:29;s:25:"Chair Table Sizing Guide.";i:30;s:116:"The British and European Standards for chairs and tables for educational institutions were approved in January 2007.";i:31;s:175:"BS EN 1729 Part 1 functional dimensions ensures furniture is the appropriate size shape and ergonomic design to maintain good posture and reduce RSI and back pain in students.";i:32;s:21:"This size mark guide.";i:33;s:136:"A counter height table is typically 34 to 36 inches tall and can be paired with counter height chairs or stools at 24 to 26 inches tall.";i:34;s:141:"Counter height chairs and stools can also be used if you have an outdoor counter space that can double as an area for eating or entertaining.";i:35;s:157:"To determine the ideal table and chair heights for your classroom keep in mind that the space between the seat height and the table should be 17 cm to 21 cm.";i:36;s:133:"This provides the most desirable amount of space for children to fit their legs under the table and to comfortably rest their elbows.";i:37;s:146:"For planning your room it is best to give between 30 36 inches per seat and a minimum of 3 feet or 36 inches between the table ends and the walls.";i:38;s:111:"If you want a room that feels more spacious 4-6 feet between the walls and the back of the chairs is suggested.";i:39;s:162:"The general rule for tables in early care and education classrooms is the space between the seat of the chair and the underside of the table should be 7-8 inches.";i:40;s:190:"Thats just the right amount of space for children to be able to fit their legs under the table and it also ensures that the table is low enough for children to comfortably rest their elbows.";i:41;s:279:"Minimum width - 24 inches 61cm per person although an economy airline tray table is about 18 inches wide Minimum depth clearance at knee level - 18 inches 46cm Minimum depth clearance at foot level - 24 inches 61cm Minimum height clearance at foot level - 4 inches 10cm Standing.";i:42;s:42:"Minimum width - 20 inches 51cm per person.";i:43;s:37:"Chair Table Spacing Tips Suggestions.";i:44;s:75:"Ft per person for spacious dining allows for a table chair and aisle 12 sq.";i:45;s:56:"Ft per person for cafeteria or restaurant-style seating.";i:46;s:57:"Ft per person for banquet institutional or close seating.";i:47;s:84:"This is because chairs are most often paired with these most common types of tables.";i:48;s:90:"Standard-height tables which are 28 30 high or counter-height tables which are 34 36 high.";i:49;s:110:"For all tables we recommend allowing for at least 12 of space between the seat of your chair and the tabletop.";i:50;s:130:"If purchasing a table or desk for a child consider purchasing a chair or chairs designed to go along with it to ensure a good fit.";i:51;s:62:"Otherwise the chair seat may be too low or high for the table.";i:52;s:111:"Ideally standard tables will have chairs that are 18 to 23 inches tall with a table thats 28 to 30 inches tall.";i:53;s:167:"However taller ones demand taller chairs or even stools counters demand chairs that are around 26 inches tall while bar stools need to be at least 28 inches in height.";i:54;s:114:"Rectangular is the most common table shape and the dimensions vary depending on how many people youd like to seat.";i:55;s:51:"Most rectangular tables are between 36 and 40 wide.";i:56;s:48:"A table that seats four should be about 48 long.";}}